According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global GaN Power Devices market was valued at USD 368 million in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 480 million in 2025 to USD 2,279 million by 2032, registering a remarkable CAGR of 27.8% during the forecast period. The market is experiencing exceptional growth as industries increasingly adopt energy-efficient power conversion technologies across electric vehicles (EVs), data centers, renewable energy systems, consumer electronics, industrial automation, and 5G telecommunications infrastructure. Gallium Nitride (GaN) power devices offer significantly higher switching speeds, greater power density, lower energy losses, and superior thermal performance compared to conventional silicon-based semiconductors, enabling the development of smaller, lighter, and more efficient power systems.
